│                                                                                                                              │
│ ### 1. Analysis of the Crash                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The crash is an assertion failure: `isa<> used on a null pointer` in `llvm::isa_impl_cl<To, const From*>::doit` where `To`   │
│ is `llvm::VPWidenCastRecipe`.                                                                                                │
│ The backtrace points to `llvm::VPPartialReductionRecipe::computeCost` as the source of the `isa<>` call.                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                       │
│ // from llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp                                                                       │
│ unsigned VPPartialReductionRecipe::computeCost(...) const {                                                                  │
│   // ...                                                                                                                     │
│   if (isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(getIngredient(0))) // CRASH HERE                                                                │
│     // ...                                                                                                                   │
│ }                                                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ This means `getIngredient(0)` is returning a null pointer. `getIngredient(0)` retrieves the first operand of the             │
│ `VPPartialReductionRecipe`.                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The reproducer shows a loop with a reduction:                                                                                │
│ `%rdx.next = add nsw i32 %rdx, %conv1`                                                                                       │
│ where `%conv1` is a `zext i8 %c to i32` defined outside the loop.                                                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The loop vectorizer builds a `VPlan` to represent the vectorized loop. For reductions, it creates `VPPartialReductionRecipe` │
│ nodes. The operands of this recipe are `VPValue`s representing the inputs to the reduction.                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The reduction operation is `add nsw i32 %rdx, %conv1`. The inputs are the previous value of the reduction variable (`%rdx`)  │
│ and the loop-invariant value `%conv1`. The `VPPartialReductionRecipe` will have two ingredients: one for `%rdx` and one for  │
│ `%conv1`.                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The `computeCost` function seems to assume that the first ingredient (`getIngredient(0)`) is the one being added to the      │
│ reduction chain, and it checks if it's a `VPWidenCastRecipe`. However, the order of ingredients is not guaranteed. In this   │
│ case, it seems the first ingredient corresponds to the reduction PHI (`%rdx`), and the second to the loop-invariant          │
│ `%conv1`.                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ When `VPlanBuilder` processes the loop-invariant `%conv1`, it creates a `VPValue` for it. Since `%conv1` is defined outside  │
│ the loop, its defining recipe is `nullptr`. This is because `VPlan` only models instructions inside the loop.                │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ When `VPPartialReductionRecipe::computeCost` is called, if the `VPValue` for `%rdx` is at index 0, `getIngredient(0)` will   │
│ be non-null. But if the `VPValue` for `%conv1` is at index 0, `getIngredient(0)` will be null because its defining recipe is │
│ null. The `isa<>` on a null pointer then triggers the assertion.                                                             │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ### 2. Proposed Fix                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The `computeCost` function for `VPPartialReductionRecipe` needs to be more robust. It should not assume a fixed order for    │
│ its ingredients. It should iterate through its ingredients and check for a `VPWidenCastRecipe`. If an ingredient is null     │
│ (which can happen for loop-invariants), it should be skipped.                                                                │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The logic should be:                                                                                                         │
│ 1. Iterate over all ingredients of the `VPPartialReductionRecipe`.                                                           │
│ 2. For each ingredient, check if it's non-null.                                                                              │
│ 3. If it's non-null, check if it's a `VPWidenCastRecipe`.                                                                    │
│ 4. If it is, add the cost of the cast and stop searching.                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ This change will make the cost computation correct regardless of the ingredient order and robust against loop-invariant      │
│ inputs that don't have a defining recipe in the VPlan.                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ### 3. Implementing the Fix                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will modify `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp`.                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The original code in `VPPartialReductionRecipe::computeCost`:                                                                │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                       │
│   // ...                                                                                                                     │
│   Instruction *RedInst = cast<Instruction>(getVPValue()->getDefiningRecipe()->getUnderlyingValue());                         │
│   Type *Ty = RedInst->getType();                                                                                             │
│   unsigned Cost = getScalarCost(RedInst);                                                                                    │
│   if (isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(getIngredient(0)))                                                                              │
│     Cost += Ctx.TTI.getCastInstrCost(Instruction::ZExt, Ty,                                                                  │
│                                      getIngredient(0)->getUnderlyingValue()->getType(),                                      │
│                                      TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput, RedInst);                                                     │
│   // ...                                                                                                                     │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The corrected code:                                                                                                          │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                       │
│   // ...                                                                                                                     │
│   Instruction *RedInst = cast<Instruction>(getVPValue()->getDefiningRecipe()->getUnderlyingValue());                         │
│   Type *Ty = RedInst->getType();                                                                                             │
│   unsigned Cost = getScalarCost(RedInst);                                                                                    │
│   for (VPValue *Ing : ingredients()) {                                                                                       │
│     if (Ing && isa<VPWidenCastRecipe>(Ing)) {                                                                                │
│       Cost += Ctx.TTI.getCastInstrCost(                                                                                      │
│           Instruction::ZExt, Ty, Ing->getUnderlyingValue()->getType(),                                                       │
│           TTI::TCK_RecipThroughput, RedInst);                                                                                │
│       break;                                                                                                                 │
│     }                                                                                                                        │
│   }                                                                                                                          │
│   // ...                                                                                                                     │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ This iterates through all ingredients, checks for null, and then checks the type. This is safe and correct.                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
